  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Human Resources Assistant (Part-Time)",
  "description": "<p><strong>About the Role:</strong><br>\nWe are seeking a <strong>Part-Time HR Assistant</strong> to support our Human Resources department, primarily in <strong>scanning and digitizing physical documents</strong>. The ideal candidate is organized, detail-oriented, and able to maintain confidentiality. In addition to document handling, the role may include ad hoc administrative support for other HR tasks when needed.</p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Scan and digitize HR documents (employee records, contracts, forms, etc.)</li>\n  <li>Systematically name, file, and organize scanned documents into digital folders</li>\n  <li>Ensure quality, accuracy, and completeness of digital files</li>\n  <li>Handle confidential and sensitive information with discretion</li>\n  <li>Assist with other HR-related administrative tasks on an ad-hoc basis.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Basic computer skills (scanning, PDFs, file organization, cloud storage, etc.)</li>\n  <li>Strong attention to detail and accuracy</li>\n  <li>Ability to work independently and handle confidential information</li>\n  <li>Prior office or administrative experience is a plus but not required</li>\n  <li>Availability for part-time hours.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>What We Offer:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Flexible working hours</li>\n  <li>Supportive team and positive working environment</li>\n  <li>Opportunity to gain hands-on HR experience</li>\n  <li>Competitive hourly rate</li>\n</ul>",
